caption: My first time here I was not disappointed the food was so great and so were the cocktails

The waiter we had was amazing!! I went through my water glass so fast and he was back instantly to refill it! We even got donuts at the end of our meal on the staff because of a super special event! I’ll definitely be back!

Music and atmosphere were great. I had the Kimchi Fried Chicken ramen and it was phenomenal. Some of the best ramen I have ever had, and I've had a lot. The ginger dressing on the salad was also very good. The salmon rice wasn't bad at all but not my favorite. The waitress was very kind but very busy.
The food is always amazing... pork belly is to die for

We had to sit outside due to pandemic “season”. Though it had heater but it was still cold. Thank God Ramen came and warmed us up. We ordered two different kind of ramens. Both are great, just wish that a bit more flavor to it. Service is quick and friendly! Will be back maybe when the indoor opens back up..
Pretty legit ramen. I did the tonkatsu tonkotsu with fried garlic, and it was awesome.

Really enjoyed the food! The yuzu sake bomb was really good. We were pleasantly surprised at how much we enjoyed the karagge chicken nugget appetizer. We would definitely order that again. We went on a cold night and were seated by the door, so the restaurant was drafty for most of the evening. Bring a jacket!
Ate here for the 1st time and never ate Ramen from a restaurant and it was fantastic. I definitely will eat there again when in Chicago again.
Third visit there, the staff are really friendly and the food is excellent. With fast service as well, what is not to like?

It's been more than a year that I revisited this place, of course, cuz of lockdown. Finally was able to get in the place instead of taking out. I am happy to say that they have not only maintained their quality of food and service but have amped up their covid cleanliness. I am so glad I planned my dinner here. Looking forward to more visits. Thanks guys!
Great good, very covid safe. It was the first time I've eaten out sine the pandemic and I felt totally safe. Great experience!
Our server was awesome! Music was fantastic, all around great place
Holy God this place was the most amazing ramen I've ever had. You must go here!
Delicious and the service is amazing!!!!
Superb Ramen! Loved the music and vibe of the restaurant.
Most certainly my favorite ramen spot in Chicago
Delicious 🤤
Tasty ramen. We got the pork belly ramen lunch meal that came with kaarage chicken and a salad. I would definitely love to go here again. Also, indoor dining 😋

the person who greets you was very nice and kind. we got our order for carry out and they had forgot to put them in the box but we called and they were very accommodating. food was fantastic. ramen was delicious, chicken and veggie dumplings were very good and the sushi was great also. definitely cant wait to eat there again

I have never felt more discriminated in my life before, i enter the place and waiting for the lady as she was talking to another customer in front of me I was talking to my family in spanish and then the lady started asking me questions of were i come from, she asked me if I had a mask i told her yes, she asked if I had Covid I told her no then she asked me where I came from and I said florida and she told me we can't serve you sir, you will have to go, i didn't even have any interaction whatsoever just the spanish speaking with my family which she heard and since that moment she came and told me you need to go, i guess the ramen is good but not for Latino or spanish speakers.
Disappointed....
This place is amazing! Everything we tried was absolutely delicious. The atmosphere was romantic with the lighting and music.  AND they have the dining room open right now!  Thank you Ramen-san!

This place is so perfect for Ramen Lovers. Many options available. They have appetizers, mantou buns, bao and ramen. I tried Thai Wings, Kimchi and Fried Chicken Ramen, Tonkotsu Ramen Bowl and Mini Donuts with Miso Caramel dip. Everything was just perfect and delicious. Indoor dining available due to special permissions. Must visit..!! 🙂
Great place good beer and sake also staff was excellent.
Love it .... customer service beautiful see you soon
The Ramen is very good
Great food, nice staff. Does get busy on a Friday night.
great ambiance & decor. looking forward to a return visit. feels similar to a cafe in chicago i liked.
not authentic japanese ramen, but the miso salmon rice and the veggie ramen was really yummy! fast service. recommend. gyoza good too.
Great Ramen noodles especially on a cold day. The kimchi fried chicken ramen was fabulous.

I love this place! Each time I'm in the area, this is my favorite lunch spot. The best part is their lunch special last longer than the other locations. I'm sure this is due to the hospital's proximity and how people have very different lunchtimes. Their staff are always very professional and provide outstanding service.
Great service, great Ramen

(Translated by Google) Good frame noodle soup, nice service. Unfortunately the hip-hop music was inappropriate and too loud.  (Original) Gute Rahmen Nudelsuppe,  nette Bedienung. Leider war die Hiphop Musik unpassend und zu laut gewesen.
do yourself a favor and give this place a try. quick and friendly service. the bill was fair i would say.

As my first time ordering ramen, I ordered from Ramen-San deluxe in Streeterville. The food was good in taste however I found a staple in my food. I ended up throwing out the food because I lost my appetite and told them about this issue. They only gave me a partial refund for my order (which didn’t even cover the cost of the item ordered with tax). Although staff was friendly I wouldn’t get food from here again, especially because they couldn’t even make it right and just offered a small partial refund.
service is always prompt even when they have a full house. the service here is friendly. the bill was reasonable i would say.
I should have took a photo of the food but it was too good to interrupt. This place has an awesome atmosphere.
As an Asian, I'd say they have the best ramen in Chicago! Service is quite friendly too! Try Tonkatsu ramen and salmon avocado maki, you won't regret.
Cool atmosphere and good food!!!
Express Lunch was a great deal and good food

Express lunch is the way to go. I got the Karrage nuggets and Tonkotsu ramen. Perfect portion size to fill you up without weighing down. The staff took temperature checks and was generally very caring about COVID-19. Would go again when I'm back in Chicago!
Honestly my favorite evening place. The bill was appropriate. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I liked.
do not leave if it's busy, it is worth it. i've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back.

I had the Shio, and it was spectacular!  My kiddo is immunocompromised and had a long day in the clinic at the children's hospital. I called Ramen-San and they were more than happy to accommodate his dietary restrictions (low bacteria). He had the Kid's Ramen with fried chicken. They blanched the noodles as well to be extra safe.  He's told me that he is full three times so far, and yet he keeps going back for another slurp of noodles. It's been a long time since he's been able to eat a full meal.  Thank you!
The deluxe is the way to go, sushi and ramen can't beat it.
Ramen is a little too garlicky, but still really delicious.

Overall a decent Ramen place located in downtown Chicago. Not the most robust menu of options but what I ordered was tasty. The restaurant was very clean and the staff was very friendly and attentive. Prices were reasonable for a very filling bowl of Ramen. I stopped in for dinner but I could see this being a great place for lunch too.

This restaurant is definitely one of the most pleasant restaurants in the neighborhood. Always when I visit this place I am very happy. They preserve their high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they provide. You no doubt will love this place. Highly  recommended.
I enjoyed every piece of it. Salty so down it with water. If you eat really fast, get ready for the GERD and bloat.
I just like their dishes. I always get awesome customer service here. The place is neat and the staff members are always very nice. Will come back again.

Service was awful, but the food was great, hence the low rating. The host was either on their first day or didn't care. Wasn't even greeted at the stand, just  handed and pointed to a seat after a long wait.
Ambience is fantastic. Sushi is okay. Pork and shrimp dumplings were delicious!!! Ramen was also good. Overall great experience!

Warm inviting Steeeterville space, pumping out hip hop, slinging ramen soups and non traditional asian appetizers. Took advantage of Lucky Hour in Steeeterville 3-6pm, ordered $3 chicken nuggets, roasted edamame chicken buns and $4 Asahi drafts. kids wanted more buns! Dinner did not disappoint, with a great maki express set with spicy tuna and crunchy tuna. Comes with a house salad, edamame and miso for $19. Enough to split for two. Great service, vibe and eye candy. Expect to spend about an hour and spend about $26-30 per person, higher with a drink or two.
Great service,  first time there,  I'll go back to taste more dishes.

The ramen is very good here. A friend and I came for dinner and made a reservation in advance, which saved us a probably 15-20min wait around 7pm. The Tonkotsu ramen broth was delicious and had great depth of flavor. The noodles were slightly overcooked. The lobster and chive dumplings were pretty, but the skins were too thick and the filling flavors didn't really stand out. My friend is vegetarian and appreciated the option of vegetarian ramen. I suppose prices were what you could expect from downtown Chicago, so I wasn't too surprised by the bill. Service was friendly and the wait wasn't too long for food.

Amazing ramen , the best I have had. The artichoke side was to die for. Very nice experience , will definitely recomend The soup was not too hot like in most restaurants it was the right temperature to start eating as soon it is served

Having visited Japan, I wouldnt say this ramen is super authentic or exceptionally good but it's pretty decent. Service is good and the portions are decent as well. Would probably still come back for ramen (unless I find a better ramen place)
Not much to say...... quick and what you would expect...
I had an extraordinary experience in this spot. We liked the superb environment and the food. The staff are very friendly. I’m happy we ultimately decided to visit this restaurant.

Music is 90's hip hop mostly. Personally was good for me. Food hit the spot! Ramen with pulled pork special was just the right spice and flavor. Staff was friendly. Food took a little long but I wasn't in a rush so It didn't bother me any. Definitely recommended

Large space with plenty of seating, cold asahi beer, well made cocktails and decent ramen and sushi. Service is a little slow. bland noodles and oily soup

Great food and fast service.
The sushi was soooo good! I absolutely love their Raman! So worth coming here!

Overall a decent place to go. The wait staff is friendly and quick.  The food itself is decent, although the ramen I had was a little lacking on meat, and small in portion size. If you care about the decor of a place, this place has a cool aesthetic. Maybe go here if in the area, but there are better ramen places in Chicago.
Good food,  excellent staff.
Great Ramen. Try the grilled edamame - delicious!

This place is lovely. Had edamame and ramen.  Pork and chicken bun both excellent, liked the pork a little more with the sriracha sauce. Will definitely put this place on rotation when in chicago.  Staff also extremely nice and attentive.

My second time at RAMEN-SAN. Previous experience being in Fulton Market, my sister and I went during the lunch to dinner odd time. We sat right away but it took a while for someone to come over to us which we understood but just thought it was strange. We were comped for the sushi which was nice but when it came to the bill my sister was charged the full amount instead of the split bill we did. Was my card not charged? Weird. Oh well, maybe it was just a bad time but it put a sour taste in my sisters mouth and she won’t be going back neither will I.

I would say I don't know enough about Ramen to say it this was good or bad this my rating. The lunchtime visit while at NW was spur of the moment. I was hungry, wanted to try something different. This is the Fried Chicken Ramen with an egg. It was plenty spicy but there was nothing about this that told me I should have more on any day. I can see the appeal to a hungry college kid but I bought something else when I was hungry and in college. The flavor is there but I wasn't impressed as much as I had hoped. It was an "Eh!" experience for me. Again I blame my own ignorance. Would I go again? Sure but I would want to try something more substantial if they had it otherwise I think I would pass. ‍

We had a great time! Excellent food and service, and the prices are very reasonable.  Can’t wait to go back.

The eggplant fries were really good though.  We won't be coming back, there are competitors in the neighborhood that do a much better bowl of ramen.
Quality ramen and sushi in the same place. I took out the pork from my spicy ramen and it made it significantly less spicy, but the waiter was nice to bring me the spice with no charge
So cool and delicious 😋
Tasty lunch and great ambience. Very nice cool spot near hospital in Streeterville

I arrive at this marvelous  place many times  as I enjoy the good air that is outline this place. The personel is very welcoming and well trained. The service is very efficient. I had the ramen at around 5-6pm and felt nauseous since then. Now at 1:14am I just vomit every single ramen out. I won’t forget the taste of the ramen forever. Though the service was good.
Good food

By FAR the best pork belly I've ever had! The fried chicken kimchi ramen was also delicious! If you're craving ramen in Chicago, then you must visit this place!  Everything was so well done, our server was great, and the atmosphere inside the restaurant is terrific. Next time I'm in Chicago, I'll be back!

We had the tonkatsu and breaded chicken curry ramens. The vibe in the room was so good even for it being dinner rush. The staff were so kind when one of their sesame grinders broke in my ramen, they got me a new one on the house even after I said it was not needed.
The ramen portions are huge and the sushi delicious.

I am absolutely in love with this place, the food was served in a timely manner and the flavor was amazing!!! , our server mellow was very helpful on selecting the Tonkotsu is wonderful , but what stood out most was his customer service skills he made me feel like I was already a regular now I don’t live in Chicago but I know when I come back soon I gotta stop in to see Mellow and get some more Tonkotsu
I love this place! The servers are very knowledgeable about the menu, ingredients, and allergy friendly. They finally have rice noodles! Gluten and allergy friendly.

I will start by saying the wait staff were extremely friendly! I am a lover of Japanese food, but I found that both the ramen and steamed bun I had were lacking in flavor. The ramen was not spicy even though I added chili. The pork belly had an odd texture and tasted more like cured bacon and less like traditional pork chasu.
delicious fresh ramen!! as a plus, they were very accommodating to my vegan diet!

Great spot! I appreciate the staff being accommodative and attentive to my allergies. I enjoy the lunch options and appreciate the “Deluxe” part of the menu. (I do miss the red dragon special at ‘Mr. Maki’ which used to be attached.) Also, love the throwback music and would love to follow their playlist.

Sad presentation of ramen. Broth was pretty bad, like a home made first try that didn't go as planned. So disapointing, since we love ramen and were looking forward trying this place out. Waiter was awkard and barely stopped by our table. Like he was wearing an ear piece and someone was giving him instructions and sometimes telling him jokes (he would laugh to himself out of nowhere). Ambiance is a bad version of furious spoon. Not coming back.
Poor service.
Over priced for what you get. I've had better ramen.
Amazingly rich ramen and sumptuous sushi.

I  did a delivery order from here. I ordered two mantou buns: a fried chicken and a pork belly. The fried chicken mantou bun was delicious. The chicken was very well made! The only critic would be adding some sort of sauce so it’s not as dry. The fried pork belly mantou bun did have a sauce. The bun was soft and pillowy. The fried pork skin was super crispy. The pork was well prepared so it just melted in my mouth. I could’ve used just a bit more crisp for both meats on my buns. The bun and meat combo can be a lot of softness without a crispy element, and my cucumbers weren’t as crispy as I was expecting so the only crisp I got on the pork bun was the few moments biting into the pork skin. Same for the fried chicken bun, but the crisp is something not everyone needs a lot of. So i guess it’s better to do it this way and next time I can just ask for crispier. I also got the sumo bowl and added fried garlic and buttered corn. I like more corn so I added some. The fried garlic on top was such a good addition. The flavor was magnificent added with that broth and chashu!! I did NOT care for the xo wontons. When I bit into it, the taste was like old, spoiled seafood, and that’s the taste I got. It tasted like nasty shrimp. I didn’t care for it. I took that one bite, and threw the rest out. This was my first time eating a ramen bowl but I’ve always wanted to try them. This place did not disappoint. I would definitely eat from here again. Overall, with a few adjustments to my order, I would do an order from here again. It was delicious. I’m satisfied.  Edit: Response to owner. No, I got no additional sauces. The food was still tasty though. Thank you for taking the time out to respond!!
Friendly, great food, awesome 90s music. Beautiful, like stepping back in time almost it  was awesome. I will be going back again and I'm bringing friends and family.
Delicious place!!!
Love the tempura and ramen! Good taste and reasonable price. It is out of my expectation. Definitely will go there again.
Great options of ramen! And nicely busy in these holidays))
If I am just reviewing for the food quality, I would have go for 2 star.

Can't say anything about the food because unfortunately  we didn't get to eat it. I made my research on Thanksgiving  - looking that the place was indeed open  - and then I went to the website and reserved a place for a group of four. I got a confirmation email AND a reminder. All this plus the drive to place plus parking only to find out that the place is closed shut. Very frustrating! Sloppy management and bad experience.

I gave the service 5 stars. But as for the ramen itself, I guessed I could only give 3. We were looking for authentic Japanese ramen, but their ramen was much affected by American food. If it was named soup noodle but not ramen, I would give it 4. If you were looking for good place soup noodle, I’d recommend it, but definitely a no if you were looking for Japanese ramen.

The best ramen restaurant. Amazing service and the food was fresh and delicious. Would come back.
I've been to to this place 5 times and I've had excellent service ❤️
Good food.

Very good host. Welcoming place. But food was just not good, and it came very slowly. Okonomiyaki was nothing like the original recipe (expect an extra fat pancake). Edit note : I felt like 2 stars was a bit harsh, as it wasn't necessarily a bad experience, even though we were disappointed. I bumped it up to 3 stars.

Food here is good as always. Simple menu, delicious ramen, and awesome ambiance. Had an order in our group that wasn't as good and had an egg shell in it, but the staff actually removed it from our bill and brought out fresh ramen just to make it up to us.
Went out to lunch and had the lunch express. It was worth it!

Horrible, can't follow instructions. I ordered Kimchi and fried chicken ramen and I asked for no scallions and got extra. Paid for extra chicken and got less and on top of that it was missing the corn. Broth was cold and one of them had a piece of paper inside it.

I have never written a review on Google but we had a really bad experience this last time we ordered takeout. We got the tonkotsu ramen and the maki express set. The tonkotsu ramen was so unbearably salty that it made my skin itch! The maki sushi was great - but the side salad was terribly small and flavorless, the miso soup (like the ramen) was too salty, and the edamame only came with 10 pieces. This place could be so much better if they balanced the salt with other flavors! Also too much garlic in the ramen (way too much compared to other great ramen restaurants in the city). Went here for their express lunch.  For $15 you get your choice of a rice plate, one ramen, small salad-san, and marinated cucumbers.  One of the best deals you can get in the area.  The old school hip hop music that was playing that day was amazing!  From their menu:  All ramen are served with Tokyo wavy noodles from Sun Noodle.  I opted for the miso salmon and the tonkotsu (pork broth, chashu pork, and molten egg).  We also added lobster dumplings (4 pieces for $6) and an order of xoxo shrimp & pork with dried scallop, and berkshire ham for $9.  Everything was delicious, the only thing I would skip next time would be the lobster dumplings, (just not worth the price imho).   Service is very fast, if you need to watch your time, you will be in and out with time to spare.  Right now if you sign up for their email newsletter, you can get $10.00 off your next visit.  All in all, if you are craving ramen around lunch time, their express lunch cannot be beat.

I would like to think to think I am relatively well versed with ramen. I'm from California (we have a lot of ramen places) and have been to multiple regions of Japan multiple times. I've only tried their tonkotsu and spicy miso broths, but they were both very good. They got a really nice depth of flavor on the tonkotsu. I ordered firm noodles and they didn't disappoint. The proportion of both noodles and pork given were great. Some places will skimp on either. We also had the karaage which was tasty and crispy and the sauce it came with was great as well. We got the brussel sprouts, which are deep fried, and they were delicious as well. Finally, service was excellent. Bonus points for providing a lobster chair for my infant. Another option for very tasty ramen in Chicago. The staff was friendly and very attentive without being overly so. The atmosphere was very pleasant too (provided you like classic hip-hop,) with a large space with a more industrial ambiance to it, and the music selection is on point if you like classic hip-hop. They have a very well stocked bar, focusing on whiskeys, particularly Japanese whiskeys.  The only negative was that I found the ramen to be much less composed than many of the other options in the city, and it really looked like someone quickly put the different ingredients in the bowl, and poured in some broth. It didn't impact the flavor, which was very good, but if other restaurants can assemble their ramen with a higher level of care, why can't Ramen-San?  I don't think this is the best ramen in Chicago, and it won't become a go-to destination for me, but I also wouldn't tell anyone not to go there.
